The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, March 12: Sebi today clamped down on the Tayal group, the promoters of the Bank of Rajasthan, for fraudulently hiking its stake in group firm Jaybharat Textile amp; Real Estate. Sebi banned Jaybharat along with 30 other entities, which include several members of the Tayal family, from accessing the stock markets. The Tayal group, which is already facing inquiries from both Sebi and the RBI, allegedly used a clutch of entities to fraudulently bolster its holding in Jaybharat. While the Tayals informed the regulator and the bourses that it held only 67.05 per cent in the firm, a probe revealed that its actual holding was 96.99 per cent.                            
	 Washington, March 12: The RBI has entered into an agreement to buy notes worth up to $10 billion from the International Monetary Fund to help the multilateral agency shore up its resources for assisting countries hit by the global meltdown. The notes, denominated in special drawing rights, will have a maximum maturity of five years.                            
	 Calcutta, March 12: The management and workers unions of Jessop amp; Co Ltd have signed a long-term wage settlement, resulting in an immediate salary hike for the workers.                             
	 Calcutta, March 12: Phillips Carbon Black plans to raise Rs 200 crore through a QIP issue in addition to a Rs 25-crore preferential issue.                                                                                                                          
